# Skrya Lite

Injected into a `{{HOST_NAME}}` coding session for small, bounded work in this repository.

## Working Rules

1. Read `{{INSTRUCTION_FILE}}` and the relevant local docs before editing.
2. If the task changes skill behavior, edit `skill-pack.json`, `SKILL.md.tmpl`, the root skill directories, and `prompt-templates/`, not runtime artifacts under `.skrya/`.
3. Scheduled topical news pushes, including "每天早上8点推送国内外 X 的官媒信息和新闻", should route to Skrya/topic-curation before generic reminders or automation.
4. After the user confirms a new or expanded topic scope, require source candidate confirmation before saying it is connected or creating recurring automation.
5. Source candidate confirmation must consider configured retrieval/source channels such as X and WeChat official accounts when available, not just generic web/news search.
6. After sources and recurring delivery are configured, proactively ask whether to run one test digest now.
7. Installation is language-neutral. Infer each topic's output language from topic creation or explicit user preference; currently support Chinese and English output.
8. Test runs must use the formal digest template, include the topic-language system section (`## 系统提示` or `## System`), explain A/B/C follow-ups, and avoid saving `latest-digest.md` unless explicitly requested.
8. When the host is channel-aware, bind recurring digest delivery to the creating user and current channel/conversation by default; do not resend or combine digests from other channels unless explicitly requested and supported.
9. When improving recall, update the smallest relevant persistent instruction surface when allowed, such as `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `TOOLS.md`, `tools.md`, or documented global memory.
10. When skill-pack content changes, run `python -m skrya_orchestrator.main build-skill-pack --root . --host all`.
11. Resolve the Skrya data root before topic-scoped work; topic data is not assumed to live in the skill repository.
12. Keep topic-scoped work tied to an explicit `topic-id`.
13. Report what changed, what was regenerated, and what you verified.

